'''East Africa''' or '''Eastern Africa''' is the [[east|easternmost]] [[region]] of the [[Africa]]n [[continent]], variably defined by [[geography]] or [[geopolitics]]. "East Africa" commonly refers to [[Kenya]], [[Tanzania]] and [[Uganda]], and sometimes [[Rwanda]] and [[Burundi]], whereas "Eastern Africa", a [[UN]] [[subregion|scheme of geographic regions]], refers to 19 territories throughout the eastern part of Africa:
* [[Kenya]], [[Tanzania]], and [[Uganda]] – also members of the [[East African Community]] (EAC)
* [[Djibouti]], [[Eritrea]], [[Ethiopia]], and [[Somalia]] – often reckoned as the [[Horn of Africa]] * [[Mozambique]] and [[Madagascar]] – sometimes considered part of [[Southern Africa]]
* [[Malawi]], [[Zambia]], and [[Zimbabwe]] – sometimes included in [[Southern Africa]] and formerly of the [[Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland|Central African Federation]]
* [[Burundi]] and [[Rwanda]] – sometimes considered part of [[Central Africa]]
* [[Comoros]], [[Mauritius]], and [[Seychelles]] – small island nations in the [[Indian Ocean]]
* [[Réunion]] and [[Mayotte]] – [[French overseas departments and territories|French overseas territories]] also in the Indian Ocean
